%body
  .container
    .span8
      %h1 Morning Pages
      %h3 usage
      %ol
        %li
          Install the morning pages gem:
          %br
          %br
          %pre
            gem install morning-pages
          %br
        %li
          Type your words using your
          %a{:href => 'http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Guide_to_Unix/Environment_Variables#EDITOR'} $EDITOR.
          Try and get to 750 words: that's about
          %a{:href => 'http://paperartstudio.tripod.com/artistsway/id3.html'}
            three pages.
        %li
          When you are done for the moment, quit your editor. Your progress will automatically be uploaded here.
        %li
          %b Coming soon:
          Lots of lovely stats and leaderboards. We're collecting stats now, so as we add reporting to the website, your historical stats will show up.
        %li
          The entire project is open source: feel free to contribute to
          %a{:href => "http://github.com/chrismdp/morning-pages"} the gem
          or provide some reporting for
          %a{:href => "http://github.com/chrismdp/morning-pages"} the website
          should you wish to.
      %h3 why?
      %p
        I've been using the excellent
        %a{:href => 'http://750words.com'} 750words.com
        for some years, but decided I wanted to keep my words offline on my laptop. I needed:
        %ul
          %li an easy way of editing a new file for each day
          %li motivational statistics that were published to the internet, to keep me accountable.
        The morning-pages gem was born.
      %h3 about

      %p
        by
        %a#blogLink{:href => 'http://chrismdp.com'} chrismdp
        %br
